            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_d06fcff5bd64b3444f0a125b8d697e35">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This accession consists of an order book presumably kept by Nathan Whiting while on a march with British and Colonial troops from Lake Ontario in New York to Montreal, Canada, during the French and Indian War. Information is given on routine army matters, camp life, deserters, court martials, inspections, and the surrender of Montreal by the French to the British.</p>
            </scopecontent>
